cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD

The paper discusses a novel approach to visually locate bodies of research within the sciences, which involves mapping scientific outputs. This approach is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybernetics (cs.CY), and software development (cs.SD). The paper also mentions universities, corporations, funding agencies, and research topics, which further supports the relevance of these sub-categories.
